  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Amend your ways and your doings, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " i.e. mend your manners. Amending signifies both to turn from our evil works, and make our good better. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "I will cause you to dwell in this place; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " you shall not go into captivity, implying that otherwise they should; he will continue their habitations to them from age to age, as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Jeremiah 7:7",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Jeremiah 7:7",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The doing of a thing in Scripture often implies the continuance of it: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Leviticus 26:11",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Leviticus 26:11",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "I will set my tabernacle, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " i.e. I will continue it. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
